Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1595
H.P. 1053 House of Representatives, April 10, 2025
Complaints Regarding Aquaculture
Reference to the Committee on Marine Resources suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative RIELLY of Westbrook.
Cosponsored by Representatives: ANKELES of Brunswick, HASENFUS of Readfield,
LOOKNER of Portland, MILLIKEN of Blue Hill, PLUECKER of Warren, SIMMONS of
Waldoboro, TERRY of Gorham.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 17 MRSA §2807, sub-§1, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 99, §1, is amended
3 to read:
4 A. "Commercial fishing activity" means an activity directly related to a commercial
5 fishing fisheries business as defined in Title 12, section 6001, subsection 6-A or a
6 commercial activity commonly associated with or supportive of commercial fishing or
7 aquaculture, such as the manufacture or sale of ice, bait, traps, cages or nets or the
8 manufacture, installation or repair of boats, engines or other equipment commonly used
9 on boats or in facilities that involve the catching, transporting, buying, selling or
10 processing of seafood for commercial purposes.
11 Sec. 2. 17 MRSA §2807, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 99, §1, is repealed.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill amends the law that prohibits private nuisance actions against a person
1144 engaged in a commercial fishing activity or commercial fishing operation to include
1155 activities associated with aquaculture and commercial fisheries businesses, which include
1166 enterprises concerned with the commercial harvest of wild or aquacultured marine
1177 organisms.
